## `tv()` — same group-by-concern rule

Use **arrays of grouped strings** for `base`, `slots`, và `variants` whenever it improves scanability. Mỗi variant value tuân theo cùng argument order như `cn()`.

```tsx
const button = tv({
  base: [
    "inline-flex items-center justify-center",
    "rounded-md border",
    "px-4 py-2",
    "text-sm font-medium",
    "transition-colors outline-none",
    [
      "focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring",
      "disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
    ],
  ],
  variants: {
    intent: {
      primary: [
        "border-transparent bg-primary text-primary-foreground",
        "hover:bg-primary/90",
      ],
      ghost: [
        "border-transparent bg-transparent",
        "hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
      ],
    },
    size: {
      sm: ["h-8 px-3", "text-xs"],
      md: ["h-9 px-4", "text-sm"],
      lg: ["h-10 px-6", "text-base"],
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: {
    intent: "primary",
    size: "md",
  },
})
```

For components with **slots** (`slots: { root, label, … }`), apply the same group order per slot string.
